doc: The status gives a rough indication of the completion of a running print operation.

members.doc: The printing has not started yet; this status is set initially, and while the print dialog is shown.
members.name: initial

members.doc: This status is set while the begin-print signal is emitted and during pagination.
members.name: preparing

members.doc: This status is set while the pages are being rendered.
members.name: generating_data

members.doc: The print job is being sent off to the printer.
members.name: sending_data

members.doc: The print job has been sent to the printer, but is not printed for some reason, e.g. the printer may be stopped.
members.name: pending

members.doc: Some problem has occurred during printing, e.g. a paper jam.
members.name: pending_issue

members.doc: The printer is processing the print job.
members.name: printing

name: PrintStatus
